This repository contains three nearest-neighbor codes for estimation 
of photometric redshifts.
Installation instructions for each code are in the file INSTALLATION in 
the corresponding directory.


----------------------------------------------------------------
Credits
----------------------------------------------------------------

The codes presented here were written by Carlos Cunha and Charles Stibitz. 
The Kd-tree code used in all programs was written by C. Stibitz based on 
Numerical Recipes 3rd edition, W. H. Press et al. 2007. The use of the 
Kd-tree for nearest neighbor searches and their subsequent application to 
photometric redshifts was developed by C. Cunha, M. Lima, H. Oyaizu, H. Lin 
and J. Frieman.

----------------------------------------------------------------
Acknowledgements 
----------------------------------------------------------------


If using any of these codes for scientific publications please acknowledge the papers where each program was first used.

For NNE, please cite: 
Photometric Redshift Error Estimators¡ H. Oyaizu, C. E. Cunha, M. Lima, H. Lin, J. A. Frieman, 2008, ApJ, 689, 709-720 [astro-ph0711.0962].

For the weights code:
Estimating the Redshift Distribution of Faint Galaxy Samples: Weighting Training Set Objects¡M. Lima, C. E. Cunha, H. Oyaizu, E. S. Sheldon, H. Lin, J. A. Frieman 2008, MNRAS, 390, 118-130 [astro-ph0801.3822]

For the pofz code:
Estimating the Redshift Distribution of Faint Galaxy Samples - II: Applications and tests of a new method¡ C. E. Cunha, M. Lima, H. Oyaizu, J. A. Frieman, H. Lin 2009, MNRAS, 396, 2379-2398 [astro-ph0810.2991]

